		   <br /><nobr><span class="notbold">Score</span>: Decent [3.00]</nobr><br /><br /><a href="/cgi-bin/pm.pl?action=addtolist&addname=nanamusa&type=Address" id="fs8"><img src="/shared/plus.gif" border="0" align="middle" height="9" width="9" alt="Add to address book"> Add to address book</a><br /><img src="/shared/transp.gif" width="135" border="0" height="1"></td><td valign="top" class="mform2" width="100%">
<p>If you are a Half- Elf I would think you follow Tunare, if so looking at buying the Imbued koada mithril is good when you can. <br /> <br />At 27 you need to replace your newbie armour and, as you said, you need Dex, you also must make sure that your Cha is ample, it is the bards second most important stat. <br /> <br />For dex there is a great little item called the Seawind Necklace that you can pick up very cheaply and it has 15 dex. <br /> <br />There are many good jewelery items for Dex but you have alot of armour spaces, another great and cheap item is knotted belt of the ravenous, also adds dex.</p>
