		   <tr><td valign="top" id="fs8" class="mform" ><span class="notbold">By:</span> <a href="/db/poster.html?user=247125"><span id="Scholar">Jiggidyjay of the Seven Seas</span></a><b><span id="Scholar"><br>Scholar</span></b><br /><img src="/shared/user_star_ico.gif" height="9" width="9" alt="*" /><img src="/shared/user_star_ico.gif" height="9" width="9" alt="*"/><img src="/shared/user_star_ico.gif" height="9" width="9" alt="*" /><br />1950 posts
		   <br /><nobr><span class="notbold">Score</span>: Good [4.14]</nobr><br /><br /><a href="/cgi-bin/pm.pl?action=addtolist&addname=Jiggidyjay&type=Address" id="fs8"><img src="/shared/plus.gif" border="0" align="middle" height="9" width="9" alt="Add to address book"> Add to address book</a><br /><img src="/shared/transp.gif" width="135" border="0" height="1"></td><td valign="top" class="mform" width="100%">
<p><blockquote><b class="sm">Quote:</b><hr size="1" />you need Dex, you also must make sure that your Cha is ample, it is the bards second most important stat. <hr size="1" /></blockquote> <br /> <br />Actually, charisma has more to do with missed notes then dex does. There were some huge parses on it done over on the concert hall, but that was before they switched over to the new forums, so it's not there anymore. I'll ask around and see if anybody can repost any of the parses. It turns out Dex really isn't that important for bards. It still helps learn melee skills quicker, but those really aren't that hard to keep up. We know now that it has no effect on procs either, as many used to think. It supposedly does effect crits, but since you can't crit until you get the proper AA's... so I would go with the bone dust gauntlets. Not only does it have AC, it has STA. STA and HP are your friends and are THE most important things for EVERY class. <br /> <br /><i><span class="sm">Edited, Sun Sep 26 19:09:26 2004 by Jiggidyjay</span></i></p>
